<title>13.11.2020 Computer stopped working a few days before submitting an assignment? Students may borrow faculty laptops</title>
<link>https://www.fit.vut.cz/fit/news/2941/</link>
<description>What to do when your laptop breaks down before 
submitting an assignment and when there is currently no access to computer 
laboratories? Students who have to face such a problem can now borrow faculty 
laptops. &amp;quot;A student who gets into an awkward situation when, for example, they 
have no device they can use to work on their projects due to a malfunction, can 
ask the FIT library, which will provide a laptop in co-operation with the 
Computer Centre, as well as prepare a loan record. The student can then visit 
the library during opening hours to sign the record at the distribution point 
and pick up the laptop. The loan is intended for the necessary period before 
the student's computer is repaired, or before the student buys a new computer, 
so we expect they will have the laptop for a month at most,&amp;quot; explains Bohuslav 
Křena, Vice-Dean for Efficiency and Academic Affairs.&amp;nbsp;</description>
